#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.230"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.230:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.230:0.2"
msgid "18. Samuddavagga"
msgstr "18. The Ocean"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 230. Bāḷisikopamasutta → bāḷisiko (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.230:0.3"
msgid "230. Bāḷisikopamasutta"
msgstr "230. The Simile of the Fisherman"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.159"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.230:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, bāḷisiko āmisagatabaḷisaṃ gambhīre udakarahade "
"pakkhipeyya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose a fisherman was to cast a baited hook into a deep lake."

msgctxt "sn35.230:1.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ aññataro āmisacakkhu maccho gileyya."
msgstr "Seeing the bait, a fish would swallow it."

msgctxt "sn35.230:1.3"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, maccho gilitabaḷiso bāḷisikassa anayaṃ āpanno byasanaṃ "
"āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo bāḷisikassa."
msgstr ""
"And so the fish that swallowed the hook would meet with tragedy and "
"disaster, and the fisherman can do what he wants with it."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: vadhāya → vyābādhāya (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.230:2.1"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, chayime baḷisā lokasmiṃ anayāya sattānaṃ vadhāya "
"pāṇinaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are these six hooks in the world that mean tragedy "
"and slaughter for living creatures."

msgctxt "sn35.230:2.2"
msgid "Katame cha?"
msgstr "What six?"

msgctxt "sn35.230:2.3"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasant, sensual, and arousing."

# Here bhikkhu is punctuated as vocative, but the sutta is addressed to bhikkhave, so it must be nominative.
msgctxt "sn35.230:2.4"
msgid "Tañce, bhikkhu, abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,"

msgctxt "sn35.230:2.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gilitabaḷiso, mārassa anayaṃ āpanno "
"byasanaṃ āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe …"
msgstr ""
"they’re called a mendicant who has swallowed Māra’s hook. They’ve met with "
"tragedy and disaster, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them."

msgctxt "sn35.230:2.6"
msgid "santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …."
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.230:3.1"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.230:3.2"
msgid "Tañce, bhikkhu, abhinandati abhivadati ajjhosāya tiṭṭhati."
msgstr "If a mendicant approves, welcomes, and keeps clinging to them,"

msgctxt "sn35.230:3.3"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu gilitabaḷiso mārassa anayaṃ āpanno byasanaṃ "
"āpanno yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato."
msgstr ""
"they’re called a mendicant who has swallowed Māra’s hook. They’ve met with "
"tragedy and disaster, and the Wicked One can do what he wants with them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.230:4.1"
msgid ""
"Santi ca, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, "
"pleasant, sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.230:4.2"
msgid ""
"Tañce, bhikkhu, nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati. Ayaṃ vuccati, "
"bhikkhave, bhikkhu na gilitabaḷiso mārassa abhedi baḷisaṃ paribhedi baḷisaṃ "
"na anayaṃ āpanno na byasanaṃ āpanno na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato … pe …."
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, they’re "
"called a mendicant who hasn’t swallowed Māra’s hook. They’ve broken the "
"hook, destroyed it. They haven’t met with tragedy and disaster, and the "
"Wicked One cannot do what he wants with them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.230:5.1"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, jivhāviññeyyā rasā … pe …."
msgstr "There are sounds … smells … tastes … touches …"

msgctxt "sn35.230:5.2"
msgid ""
"Santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā "
"kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā."
msgstr ""
"thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, "
"sensual, and arousing."

msgctxt "sn35.230:5.3"
msgid ""
"Tañce bhikkhu nābhinandati nābhivadati nājjhosāya tiṭṭhati, ayaṃ vuccati, "
"bhikkhave, bhikkhu na gilitabaḷiso mārassa abhedi baḷisaṃ paribhedi baḷisaṃ "
"na anayaṃ āpanno na byasanaṃ āpanno na yathākāmakaraṇīyo pāpimato”ti."
msgstr ""
"If a mendicant doesn’t approve, welcome, and keep clinging to them, they’re "
"called a mendicant who hasn’t swallowed Māra’s hook. They’ve broken the "
"hook, destroyed it. They haven’t met with tragedy and disaster, and the "
"Wicked One cannot do what he wants with them.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.230:5.4"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
